---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BlogStyles from '../../components/BlogStyles.astro';
---

<Layout title="Getting Started with Python - Coding with Eric">
    <BlogStyles />
    <main>
        <h1 class="blog-title">Getting Started with <span class="text-gradient">Python</span></h1>
        <div class="blog-content">
            <p>Here's a step-by-step guide to set up Python on your computer:</p>

            <div class="blog-section">
                <h3>Step 1: Download Python</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Go to the official Python website: <a href="https://www.python.org" target="_blank" class="external-link">python.org</a></li>
                    <li>Click on the <strong>Downloads</strong> tab
                        <ul>
                            <li>The website will suggest the best version for your operating system (Windows, macOS, or Linux)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="blog-section">
                <h3>Step 2: Install Python</h3>
                <h4>For Windows:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the downloaded file (<code>python-[version].exe</code>)</li>
                    <li>Check the box <strong>"Add Python to PATH"</strong> (important)</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>Install Now</strong> and follow the prompts</li>
                </ol>

                <h4>For macOS:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the downloaded <code>.pkg</code> file</li>
                    <li>Follow the installation instructions</li>
                    <li>Open the terminal and type <code>python3 --version</code> to confirm installation</li>
                </ol>

                <h4>For Linux:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open a terminal and type:
                        <div class="code-block">
                            sudo apt update<br>
                            sudo apt install python3
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li>Confirm installation by typing:
                        <div class="code-block">
                            python3 --version
                        </div>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="blog-section">
                <h3>Step 3: Install an IDE or Text Editor</h3>
                <p>Choose a tool to write and test Python code. Popular options include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>IDLE</strong> (comes with Python)</li>
                    <li><strong>VS Code</strong>: Download from <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com" target="_blank" class="external-link">code.visualstudio.com</a></li>
                    <li><strong>PyCharm</strong>: Download from <a href="https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm" target="_blank" class="external-link">jetbrains.com/pycharm</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="blog-section">
                <h3>Step 4: Test Your Python Setup</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open your terminal or IDE</li>
                    <li>Type:
                        <div class="code-block">
                            print("Hello, World!")
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li>If you see "Hello, World!" on the screen, your setup is complete!</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <p>Now you're ready to start coding in Python! ðŸŽ‰</p>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
    main {
        margin: auto;
        padding: 1rem;
        color: white;
        font-size: 20px;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .text-gradient {
        background-image: var(--accent-gradient);
        -webkit-background-clip: text;
